def: Pertaining to a draught, or current of air; as, a draughtly,comfortless room.
A combining form used in anatomy to indicate connection with,or relation to, the styloid process of the temporal bone; as,stylohyal, stylomastoid, stylomaxillary.
Capable of being denominated or named. Sir T. Browne.
The quality or state of being sugary, or sweet.
To commove; to disturb; to stir up. [R.]Society being more or less commoted and made uncomfortable.Hawthorne.
An instrument, originally a series of bells on an iron rod, nowa set of flat metal bars, diatonically tuned, giving a bell-like tonewhen played with a mallet; a carillon.
To fortify by cutting a ditch, and raising a rampart orbreastwork with the earth thrown out of the ditch; to intrench. Pope.No more shall trenching war channel her fields. Shak.
Formed or vaulted like a beehive.
